---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why can't I get rid of cockroaches in my Cairns home myself?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Supermarket sprays kill the cockroaches you see but miss the ones breeding in wall voids, behind the fridge motor, and inside cupboards — and in the tropics they breed fast. German cockroaches in particular avoid sprayed surfaces, so a surface bomb can actually scatter them deeper into the building. Professional control combines a residual treatment with a targeted gel bait the cockroaches carry back to the harbourage, plus finding and treating the actual nest sites. That, plus the year-round Cairns breeding cycle, is why DIY rarely holds." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does cockroach or ant treatment cost in Cairns?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "2026 Cairns bands: a single-pest treatment (just cockroaches, or just ants) starts around $165–$215; combining the two is roughly $260–$290; and rolling them into a full general pest treatment with spiders and silverfish is about $250–$320 with a 12-month warranty. German cockroach infestations and large ant super-colonies sometimes need a follow-up visit, which is included in the warranty. Recurring plans work out cheaper per visit." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What ant species are common in Cairns and are they hard to treat?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Cairns sees coastal brown ants, black house ants, white-footed ants and the occasional tramp-ant super-colony, plus seasonal flying-ant swarms. Some species split their nest when sprayed (budding), which actually makes the problem worse — so we identify the species first and use the right gel or non-repellent bait that the workers carry back to the queen. Get the species and the method wrong and ants just relocate; get them right and the colony collapses." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is the German cockroach really that different?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. German cockroaches are small, breed extremely quickly, and live indoors in warm, moist spots — around the kitchen, dishwasher, fridge motor and bins. A single egg case holds dozens of young, so numbers explode in weeks in the Cairns climate. They also tend to avoid sprayed surfaces, so the right treatment is heavily gel-bait based with thorough harbourage treatment and usually a follow-up to break the breeding cycle. They are the one cockroach where a quick spray almost always fails." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Cockroach & Ant Control Cairns | Gel Bait & Residual"
  description="Cockroach and ant control across Cairns — targeted gel and residual treatment for German and American cockroaches and tropical ant species. Warranty-backed, recurring plans, free quote."
  canonical="https://cairnspestmanagement.com.au/services/cockroach-ant-control/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">German &amp; American cockroaches &middot; tropical ants</span>
      <h1>Cockroach &amp; ant control in <span class="accent">Cairns</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The two pests behind most Cairns call-outs. We treat German and American
        cockroaches and the full run of tropical ant species with targeted gel
        baits and low-odour residual sprays &mdash; finding and hitting the
        harbourage, not just the ones you can see. Warranty-backed, with recurring
        plans for year-round control. From about $165.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Treating the two pests Cairns calls about most.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">

        <h3>Cockroaches &mdash; gel does the heavy lifting.</h3>
        <p>
          There are two cockroaches that matter in a Cairns home. <strong>American
          cockroaches</strong> (the big ones) come in from drains, sub-floors,
          roof voids and garden bins &mdash; largely an external and entry-point
          problem. <strong>German cockroaches</strong> (small, fast-breeding) live
          indoors around the kitchen, dishwasher, fridge motor and bins, and they
          tend to avoid sprayed surfaces. So the core of our cockroach work is a
          <strong>targeted gel bait</strong> placed in the cracks and voids where
          they harbour &mdash; the workers feed, return and pass it on, collapsing
          the population &mdash; backed by a residual treatment of entry points and
          external harbourage. German jobs usually get a follow-up to break the
          breeding cycle.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Ants &mdash; identify the species first.</h3>
        <p>
          Cairns has a long list of nuisance ants &mdash; coastal brown ants,
          black house ants, white-footed ants, the odd tramp-ant super-colony, and
          seasonal flying-ant swarms after rain. The trap with ants is that some
          species <strong>bud</strong> &mdash; spray the trail and the colony
          simply splits and relocates, leaving you worse off. We identify the
          species, then use the right <strong>non-repellent residual or gel
          bait</strong> the foragers carry back to the queen. Done correctly the
          colony dies out rather than scattering across the yard.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Why the tropics make both worse.</h3>
        <p>
          Warmth and humidity let both pests breed all year &mdash; no winter
          knock-back &mdash; and the wet season drives them indoors looking for
          dry harbourage and food. A one-off treatment clears the current
          population but continuous breeding means re-colonisation within weeks.
          For kitchens, food handling and anyone who simply wants it gone for good,
          a <strong>recurring plan</strong> that resets the treatment on a 6 or
          12-monthly cycle is the reliable answer in Cairns.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Licensing, safety and why we do not cut corners.</h3>
        <p>
          Treatment is carried out by a licensed Queensland <strong>Pest
          Management Technician</strong> using only <strong>APVMA-registered</strong>
          products applied to label. Gel baits are placed in cracks, voids and
          hinges &mdash; deliberately out of reach of children and pets &mdash; and
          internal sprays are low-odour and safe once dry. The corner cut by cheap
          operators is a quick blanket spray with no gel baiting and no harbourage
          work; against German cockroaches and budding ants that does not just fail,
          it can spread the problem. We treat it properly and back it with a warranty.
        </p>

        <p>
          Want the full sweep including spiders and silverfish? See
          <a href="/services/general-pest-control/">general pest control</a>. Also
          dealing with rats or mice? See <a href="/services/rodent-control/">rodent
          control</a>, or check the
          <a href="/services/commercial-pest-control/">commercial program</a> for cafes and rentals.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/edmonton/">Edmonton</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/smithfield/">Smithfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/redlynch/">Redlynch</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/trinity-beach/">Trinity Beach</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/earlville/">Earlville</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cairns-region/">All Cairns Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Sort the cockroaches and ants.</h2>
        <p>Species-matched treatment, gel baiting, warranty-backed, recurring plans. Free quote on your home.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
